Of course, they came to the hands of the new owners not as a gift: every immigrant, wanting to facilitate the task of passing the tests, paid for the document 7,000 rubles.
This is two and a half times more expensive than the official examination procedure, which will cost the immigrant worker three thousand rubles.
The main task for the near future is to protect the system against corruption so that "diplomas" cannot be bought, converge government officials and rights defenders.
