The final document also mentioned the political situation in Paraguay.
"We hope that the electoral process in that country will serve to reintegrate the Union of South American Nations", which is currently excluded.
The need for Latin America to maintain itself as a region of prosperity and peace, integrated, and good relations among neighbours, was another of the issues highlighted by the summit.
In this regard, the President of Colombia, Juan Manuel Santos, said before starting his participation in the regional meeting that he hoped to meet with his pair from Nicaragua, Daniel Ortega, on Saturday in Mexico to treat the maritime dispute respectfully following a ruling by the ICJ, questioned by Bogotá.
